The hearse ferrying the body Former Kibwezi MP Kalembe Ndile. [Stephen Nzioka, Standard]  Former Kibwezi MP Kalembe Ndile is being buried today in a funeral expected to draw national and local political bigwigs from the region including Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua, Wiper party leader Kalonzo Musyoka and Kitui Governor Charity Ngilu, among others.  Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) party leader Raila Odinga is expected to attend.  Ndile’s body was transported to his rural home in Mbui Nzau, Makueni County, from the Lee Funeral Home, where the Tip party leader is to be accorded his final sendoff later today, Friday, June 11.  Ndile, 57, died at a Nairobi hospital on May 30, 2021, after a long illness. He is survived by 10 children, and six other adopted children.  Villagers, squatters mourn Kalembe Ndile in final send-off  Uhuru, Kalonzo hail Kalembe as selfless pro-poor politician  Supremacy battle intensifies ahead of Kalembe Ndile burial   Trucker claiming to be Kalembe Ndile’s son vows to attend burial Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua arrives for the burial. [Erustus Mulwa, Standard]  Kalembe Ndile's widow at Mbui Nzau, Makueni County. [Stephen Nzioka, Standard]  Kalembe burial underway. [Stephen Nzioka, Standard]  Kalembe Ndile's body arriving at Mbui Nzau. [Stephen Nzioka, Standard]  The casket bearing the remains of Former Kibwezi MP Kalembe Ndile. [Erastus Mutinda Mulwa, Standard]  Former Prime Minister Raila Odinga at Kalembe Ndile's burial in Makueni County. [Erastus Mutinda Mulwa, Standard]      Misa ya wafu kwa aliyekuwa mbunge wa Kibwezi Kalembe Ndile ilifanyika hii leo  Kalembe Ndile and Governor Alfred Mutua lead Kambas to a new movement  Motion to censure house speaker Justin Muturi thwarted by the government side By Mwangi Maina | 1 hour ago By Mireri Junior | 2 hours ago By Julius Chepkwony and Daniel Chege | 5 hours ago By Amos Kareithi | 7 hours ago